    a: 0,
    r: "Early mobilization after total knee replacement is essential to prevent complications such as deep vein thrombosis, joint stiffness, and muscle atrophy. Pre-medicating with prescribed analgesics 30 minutes before therapy allows the medication to take effect, making therapy more tolerable. Canceling therapy delays recovery. Dismissing the client's pain is not therapeutic. Occupational therapy does not replace the need for physical therapy post-joint replacement.",
