    r: "Daily foot inspection is the most critical component of diabetic foot care because peripheral neuropathy may prevent the client from feeling injuries. Early detection of cuts, blisters, or skin changes prevents infections that could lead to amputation. Hot water soaks can cause burns due to neuropathy. Trimming calluses with sharp blades risks injury and infection. Walking barefoot increases the risk of unnoticed trauma.",
