    a: 0,
    r: "The abdomen provides the fastest and most consistent insulin absorption due to its rich blood supply and relatively stable blood flow regardless of activity level. The outer thigh and upper arm have moderate absorption rates. The buttock has the slowest absorption rate. Consistent site rotation within one anatomical area is recommended to prevent lipodystrophy.",
    s: "Endocrine"
