    a: 0,
    r: "Hypoglycemia triggers a sympathetic nervous system response causing shakiness, diaphoresis (sweating), tachycardia, anxiety, and confusion as the brain is deprived of glucose. These symptoms signal the need for immediate glucose intake. Excessive thirst, polyuria, and blurred vision are signs of hyperglycemia. Nausea and abdominal pain can occur with DKA. Fever and chills suggest infection.",
