    r: "Oral hypoglycemic agents such as glyburide (a sulfonylurea) are typically held on the morning of surgery because the client will be NPO, and the medication could cause hypoglycemia without food intake. The healthcare provider will give specific instructions for perioperative glucose management. Doubling the dose risks severe hypoglycemia. Permanent discontinuation is not appropriate.",
